The paper discusses challenges in runtime verification beyond software, indicating a focus on system-level analysis. This suggests a strong possibility of the paper belonging to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also mentions the need for new techniques beyond the current state of the art, indicating a potential overlap with the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. The paper discusses the process of creating monitors from specifications, suggesting a possible connection to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. The paper also mentions the need for instrumentation of the system, indicating a potential overlap with the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of traces against generated monitors, suggesting a possible connection to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category.
